<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=17293&amp;p=217631#p217631"><![CDATA[
Another thing to watch out for is where the delta counter is during your sample's playback.  If your sample isn't loud enough to reset the &quot;midpoint&quot; of the sample, this can be a thing (and even if it IS loud enough, you can tilt the data toward zero with RJDMC and FamiTracker).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=34">RushJet1</a> — Fri Apr 27, 2018 12:56 pm</p><hr />
